{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775896270745,"sessionID":"ses_284564a85ffeIsrzYYenAbACrq","part":{"id":"prt_d7baa9746001Y4G2IfXzGiUtQV","messageID":"msg_d7ba9bfcf001a45N6N0OwddVnx","sessionID":"ses_284564a85ffeIsrzYYenAbACrq","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-39d107de41504ea2a5321ff91ef85703","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec: E2E Integration Tests (AR-041)\n\n## Overview\nEnd-to-end integration tests for the agentcube project, covering the complete lifecycle of AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources through the client-go library.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### REQ-001: AgentRuntime Lifecycle Integration Tests\n\n**Description**: Verify that AgentRuntime resources can be created, retrieved, updated, status-updated, deleted, and listed through the Kubernetes API server using the client-go library.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- AgentRuntime creation succeeds with valid spec\n- AgentRuntime can be retrieved by name and namespace\n- AgentRuntime spec updates are persisted\n- AgentRuntime status updates are persisted independently of spec\n- AgentRuntime deletion removes the resource\n- AgentRuntime list operations return correct resources\n- Watch operations receive events for AgentRuntime changes\n\n**GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios**:\n\n```\nScenario: Create AgentRuntime with valid spec\n  GIVEN a configured Kubernetes clientset for agentcube runtime API\n    AND a valid AgentRuntime spec with required fields (agent type, image, resource limits)\n  WHEN the AgentRuntime is created in a test namespace\n  THEN the creation succeeds with no error\n    AND the returned AgentRuntime has a generated UID\n    AND the returned AgentRuntime has creation timestamp set\n    AND the AgentRuntime spec matches the input spec\n    AND the AgentRuntime status is initialized to empty\n\nScenario: Retrieve AgentRuntime by name\n  GIVEN an existing AgentRuntime resource in a test namespace\n  WHEN the AgentRuntime is retrieved by its name\n  THEN the retrieval succeeds with no error\n    AND the returned AgentRuntime matches the stored resource\n    AND all fields including metadata, spec, and status are preserved\n\nScenario: Update AgentRuntime spec\n  GIVEN an existing AgentRuntime resource\n    AND a modified AgentRuntime spec (e.g., updated image tag)\n  WHEN the AgentRuntime spec is updated\n  THEN the update succeeds with no error\n    AND the returned AgentRuntime has the updated spec\n    AND the AgentRuntime resourceVersion is incremented\n    AND the AgentRuntime status is preserved unchanged\n\nScenario: Update AgentRuntime status independently\n  GIVEN an existing AgentRuntime resource\n    AND an updated status (e.g., phase = Running, agentID set)\n  WHEN the AgentRuntime status is updated using UpdateStatus\n  THEN the update succeeds with no error\n    AND the returned AgentRuntime has the updated status\n    AND the AgentRuntime resourceVersion is incremented\n    AND the AgentRuntime spec is preserved unchanged\n\nScenario: Delete AgentRuntime\n  GIVEN an existing AgentRuntime resource\n  WHEN the AgentRuntime is deleted by name\n  THEN the deletion succeeds with no error\n    AND subsequent retrieval of the AgentRuntime returns \"not found\" error\n    AND the AgentRuntime is removed from list results\n\nScenario: List AgentRuntimes in namespace\n  GIVEN multiple AgentRuntime resources in a test namespace\n    AND AgentRuntime resources in other namespaces\n  WHEN AgentRuntimes are listed in the specific namespace\n  THEN the list succeeds with no error\n    AND the list contains only AgentRuntimes from that namespace\n    AND all AgentRuntimes in the namespace are present\n    AND AgentRuntimes from other namespaces are not present\n\nScenario: List AgentRuntimes cluster-wide\n  GIVEN multiple AgentRuntime resources across different namespaces\n  WHEN AgentRuntimes are listed with no namespace filter\n  THEN the list succeeds with no error\n    AND the list contains AgentRuntimes from all namespaces\n    AND all AgentRuntimes in the cluster are present\n\nScenario: Watch AgentRuntime for create events\n  GIVEN a configured Kubernetes clientset\n    AND an active watch channel for AgentRuntimes in a test namespace\n  WHEN a new AgentRuntime is created in the namespace\n  THEN the watch channel receives an ADDED event\n    AND the event contains the newly created AgentRuntime\n    AND the event type is correct (v1.Added)\n\nScenario: Watch AgentRuntime for update events\n  GIVEN an existing AgentRuntime resource\n    AND an active watch channel for AgentRuntimes in its namespace\n  WHEN the AgentRuntime spec is updated\n  THEN the watch channel receives a MODIFIED event\n    AND the event contains the updated AgentRuntime\n    AND the event type is correct (v1.Modified)\n\nScenario: Watch AgentRuntime for delete events\n  GIVEN an existing AgentRuntime resource\n    AND an active watch channel for AgentRuntimes in its namespace\n  WHEN the AgentRuntime is deleted\n  THEN the watch channel receives a DELETED event\n    AND the event contains the AgentRuntime before deletion\n    AND the event type is correct (v1.Deleted)\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-002: CodeInterpreter Lifecycle Integration Tests\n\n**Description**: Verify that CodeInterpreter resources can be created, retrieved, updated, status-updated, deleted, and listed through the Kubernetes API server using the client-go library.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- CodeInterpreter creation succeeds with valid spec\n- CodeInterpreter can be retrieved by name and namespace\n- CodeInterpreter spec updates are persisted\n- CodeInterpreter status updates are persisted independently of spec\n- CodeInterpreter deletion removes the resource\n- CodeInterpreter list operations return correct resources\n- Watch operations receive events for CodeInterpreter changes\n\n**GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios**:\n\n```\nScenario: Create CodeInterpreter with valid spec\n  GIVEN a configured Kubernetes clientset for agentcube runtime API\n    AND a valid CodeInterpreter spec with required fields (code, runtime, language)\n  WHEN the CodeInterpreter is created in a test namespace\n  THEN the creation succeeds with no error\n    AND the returned CodeInterpreter has a generated UID\n    AND the returned CodeInterpreter has creation timestamp set\n    AND the CodeInterpreter spec matches the input spec\n    AND the CodeInterpreter status is initialized to empty\n\nScenario: Retrieve CodeInterpreter by name\n  GIVEN an existing CodeInterpreter resource in a test namespace\n  WHEN the CodeInterpreter is retrieved by its name\n  THEN the retrieval succeeds with no error\n    AND the returned CodeInterpreter matches the stored resource\n    AND all fields including metadata, spec, and status are preserved\n\nScenario: Update CodeInterpreter spec\n  GIVEN an existing CodeInterpreter resource\n    AND a modified CodeInterpreter spec (e.g., updated code content)\n  WHEN the CodeInterpreter spec is updated\n  THEN the update succeeds with no error\n    AND the returned CodeInterpreter has the updated spec\n    AND the CodeInterpreter resourceVersion is incremented\n    AND the CodeInterpreter status is preserved unchanged\n\nScenario: Update CodeInterpreter status independently\n  GIVEN an existing CodeInterpreter resource\n    AND an updated status (e.g., executionResult, output)\n  WHEN the CodeInterpreter status is updated using UpdateStatus\n  THEN the update succeeds with no error\n    AND the returned CodeInterpreter has the updated status\n    AND the CodeInterpreter resourceVersion is incremented\n    AND the CodeInterpreter spec is preserved unchanged\n\nScenario: Delete CodeInterpreter\n  GIVEN an existing CodeInterpreter resource\n  WHEN the CodeInterpreter is deleted by name\n  THEN the deletion succeeds with no error\n    AND subsequent retrieval of the CodeInterpreter returns \"not found\" error\n    AND the CodeInterpreter is removed from list results\n\nScenario: List CodeInterpreters in namespace\n  GIVEN multiple CodeInterpreter resources in a test namespace\n    AND CodeInterpreter resources in other namespaces\n  WHEN CodeInterpreters are listed in the specific namespace\n  THEN the list succeeds with no error\n    AND the list contains only CodeInterpreters from that namespace\n    AND all CodeInterpreters in the namespace are present\n    AND CodeInterpreters from other namespaces are not present\n\nScenario: Watch CodeInterpreter for create events\n  GIVEN a configured Kubernetes clientset\n    AND an active watch channel for CodeInterpreters in a test namespace\n  WHEN a new CodeInterpreter is created in the namespace\n  THEN the watch channel receives an ADDED event\n    AND the event contains the newly created CodeInterpreter\n    AND the event type is correct (v1.Added)\n\nScenario: Watch CodeInterpreter for delete events\n  GIVEN an existing CodeInterpreter resource\n    AND an active watch channel for CodeInterpreters in its namespace\n  WHEN the CodeInterpreter is deleted\n  THEN the watch channel receives a DELETED event\n    AND the event contains the CodeInterpreter before deletion\n    AND the event type is correct (v1.Deleted)\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-003: Informer and Lister Integration Tests\n\n**Description**: Verify that SharedInformerFactory and listers work correctly for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources, including cache synchronization and event handling.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Informers successfully start and sync cache\n- Listers return cached resources\n- Informer event handlers receive resource changes\n- Multiple informers can share the same factory\n- Cache resync works correctly\n\n**GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios**:\n\n```\nScenario: AgentRuntime informer syncs existing resources\n  GIVEN multiple AgentRuntime resources in a test namespace\n    AND a SharedInformerFactory configured for the namespace\n    AND an AgentRuntime informer from the factory\n  WHEN the informer is started\n    AND WaitForCacheSync is called\n  THEN the cache sync completes successfully\n    AND the AgentRuntime lister returns all existing AgentRuntimes\n    AND all resources are cached with correct metadata\n\nScenario: AgentRuntime informer receives create events\n  GIVEN a started AgentRuntime informer\n    AND a registered event handler for AgentRuntimes\n  WHEN a new AgentRuntime is created\n  THEN the event handler receives an OnAdd event\n    AND the event handler is called with the new AgentRuntime\n    AND the AgentRuntime is immediately available in the lister cache\n\nScenario: AgentRuntime informer receives update events\n  GIVEN a started AgentRuntime informer with existing resources\n    AND a registered event handler for AgentRuntimes\n  WHEN an existing AgentRuntime is updated\n  THEN the event handler receives an OnUpdate event\n    AND the event handler is called with old and new objects\n    AND the updated AgentRuntime is immediately reflected in the lister cache\n\nScenario: AgentRuntime informer receives delete events\n  GIVEN a started AgentRuntime informer with existing resources\n    AND a registered event handler for AgentRuntimes\n  WHEN an existing AgentRuntime is deleted\n  THEN the event handler receives an OnDelete event\n    AND the event handler is called with the deleted AgentRuntime\n    AND the AgentRuntime is removed from the lister cache\n\nScenario: Multiple informers share same factory\n  GIVEN a SharedInformerFactory configured for a test namespace\n    AND an AgentRuntime informer from the factory\n    AND a CodeInterpreter informer from the same factory\n  WHEN both informers are started\n    AND WaitForCacheSync is called for both types\n  THEN both informers sync successfully\n    AND both listers return correct resources\n    AND the factory manages a single cache for both resource types\n\nScenario: AgentRuntime lister with label selector\n  GIVEN multiple AgentRuntime resources with different labels in a test namespace\n    AND a synced AgentRuntime lister\n  WHEN AgentRuntimes are listed with a label selector\n  THEN the list returns only AgentRuntimes matching the labels\n    AND non-matching AgentRuntimes are excluded\n\nScenario: CodeInterpreter namespace lister Get by name\n  GIVEN an existing CodeInterpreter resource in a test namespace\n    AND a synced CodeInterpreter namespace lister\n  WHEN the CodeInterpreter is retrieved by name using the namespace lister\n  THEN the retrieval succeeds with no error\n    AND the returned CodeInterpreter matches the stored resource\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-004: Error Handling and Edge Cases\n\n**Description**: Verify that the client-go library handles errors, edge cases, and invalid inputs correctly.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Invalid spec returns appropriate error\n- Resource conflicts are detected\n- Watch handles disconnection and reconnection\n- Concurrent modifications are detected\n\n**GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios**:\n\n```\nScenario: Create AgentRuntime with invalid spec\n  GIVEN a configured Kubernetes clientset\n    AND an invalid AgentRuntime spec (missing required fields)\n  WHEN the AgentRuntime creation is attempted\n  THEN the creation fails with a validation error\n    AND the error message indicates the validation failure\n    AND no AgentRuntime resource is created\n\nScenario: Update AgentRuntime with stale resourceVersion\n  GIVEN an existing AgentRuntime resource\n    AND an AgentRuntime object with an outdated resourceVersion\n  WHEN the AgentRuntime update is attempted\n  THEN the update fails with a conflict error\n    AND the error indicates resource version conflict\n    AND the AgentRuntime remains unchanged\n\nScenario: Delete non-existent AgentRuntime\n  GIVEN a configured Kubernetes clientset\n    AND a non-existent AgentRuntime name in a test namespace\n  WHEN the AgentRuntime deletion is attempted\n  THEN the deletion fails with a \"not found\" error\n\nScenario: Get non-existent CodeInterpreter\n  GIVEN a configured Kubernetes clientset\n    AND a non-existent CodeInterpreter name in a test namespace\n  WHEN the CodeInterpreter retrieval is attempted\n  THEN the retrieval fails with a \"not found\" error\n\nScenario: Watch handles server disconnection\n  GIVEN an active watch channel for AgentRuntimes\n  WHEN the API server connection is temporarily lost\n    AND then re-established\n  THEN the watch channel reconnects automatically\n    AND events continue to be received after reconnection\n    AND no duplicate events are received for the same change\n\nScenario: List with field selector\n  GIVEN multiple AgentRuntime resources in different states\n    AND a configured Kubernetes clientset\n  WHEN AgentRuntimes are listed with a field selector (e.g., status.phase=Running)\n  THEN the list succeeds with no error\n    AND the list contains only AgentRuntimes matching the field selector\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-005: Fake Client Integration Tests\n\n**Description**: Verify that fake clients work correctly for testing purposes, including CRUD operations and watch behavior.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Fake clientset supports all CRUD operations\n- Fake clients track resources in memory\n- Watch operations work with fake clients\n- Fake clients can be used in unit tests\n\n**GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios**:\n\n```\nScenario: Fake clientset creates AgentRuntime\n  GIVEN a fake clientset initialized with Scheme registration\n    AND a valid AgentRuntime spec\n  WHEN the AgentRuntime is created using the fake client\n  THEN the creation succeeds with no error\n    AND the AgentRuntime is stored in the fake client's memory\n    AND the AgentRuntime can be retrieved by name\n\nScenario: Fake clientset updates AgentRuntime\n  GIVEN a fake clientset with an existing AgentRuntime\n    AND a modified AgentRuntime spec\n  WHEN the AgentRuntime is updated using the fake client\n  THEN the update succeeds with no error\n    AND the AgentRuntime in memory reflects the update\n    AND subsequent retrieval returns the updated AgentRuntime\n\nScenario: Fake clientset deletes AgentRuntime\n  GIVEN a fake clientset with an existing AgentRuntime\n  WHEN the AgentRuntime is deleted using the fake client\n  THEN the deletion succeeds with no error\n    AND the AgentRuntime is removed from memory\n    AND subsequent retrieval returns \"not found\" error\n\nScenario: Fake clientset watch for AgentRuntimes\n  GIVEN a fake clientset\n    AND an active watch channel for AgentRuntimes\n  WHEN an AgentRuntime is created\n  THEN the watch channel receives an ADDED event\n    AND the event contains the newly created AgentRuntime\n```\n\n---\n\n## Test Infrastructure\n\n### Test Setup\n- Use `test/e2e` package\n- Require a running Kubernetes API server (can use envtest for local testing)\n- Create temporary test namespaces for isolation\n- Clean up test resources after each test\n\n### Dependencies\n- `k8s.io/client-go` for Kubernetes client\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` for generated clients\n- `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/envtest` for local test environment\n\n### Test Naming Convention\n- Test functions: `Test<ModuleName>_<ScenarioName>`\n- Subtests: `/<GIVEN/WHEN/THEN_Concise_Description>`\n\n### Assertions\n- Use `assert` package from `github.com/stretchr/testify/assert`\n- Verify no errors returned\n- Verify returned objects match expected values\n- Verify resourceVersion changes on updates\n- Verify UID and timestamps on creation","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775896270737,"end":1775896270742}}}}
